Object_Heading	Object_Text	aRequirementObjectType	Section_number	ID.Status	aResponsibility	a_EB_PO_Status	a_ZF_PO_Status
1 Team Planner			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Requirements for the Team Planner view — a swimlane calendar per resource showing task assignments and enabling drag-and-drop rescheduling.	information	1.1	PO-TP-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
1.1 Resource Swimlanes			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The Team Planner shall display one swimlane row per resource, showing the resource name in a frozen left column.	functional requirement	1.1.1	PO-TP-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Each swimlane shall show task bars positioned at the correct dates within the shared timeline.	functional requirement	1.1.2	PO-TP-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Multiple tasks assigned to the same resource shall be stacked in parallel lanes within the resource row when they overlap.	functional requirement	1.1.3	PO-TP-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Unassigned tasks shall be displayed in a separate unassigned panel at the bottom.	functional requirement	1.1.4	PO-TP-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When loading a project, the Team Planner shall display a swimlane row for every named resource even if the resource's unique ID is unavailable or raises an exception; such resources shall appear with an empty task set and shall not cause an exception.	functional requirement	1.1.5	PO-TP-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.2 Drag-and-Drop			1.2	1_2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The user shall be able to drag a task bar horizontally within a swimlane to reschedule the task.	functional requirement	1.2.1	PO-TP-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The user shall be able to drag a task bar from one resource swimlane to another to reassign the task.	functional requirement	1.2.2	PO-TP-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	During a drag operation, a ghost bar shall indicate the new position. A red ghost shall indicate when the drag target overlaps a vacation block.	functional requirement	1.2.3	PO-TP-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	After dragging a task, the Team Planner shall maintain the current scroll position and not jump to an unknown time.	functional requirement	1.2.4	PO-TP-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.3 Vacation Bands			1.3	1_3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The Team Planner shall display vacation/non-working days as semi-transparent orange blocks within the resource swimlane.	functional requirement	1.3.1	PO-TP-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.4 Conflict Highlighting			1.4	1_4_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Resource rows with task overlaps (conflicts) shall be highlighted with a light-red row background and dark-red resource name text.	functional requirement	1.4.1	PO-TP-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Conflicted resource rows shall display a solid red badge with '!'.	functional requirement	1.4.2	PO-TP-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.5 Navigation and Context Menu			1.5	1_5_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	A navigation bar above the timeline shall provide First / Today / Last scroll buttons.	functional requirement	1.5.1	PO-TP-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Right-clicking a resource name shall provide a context menu action 'Scroll timeline to first task', which scrolls the Team Planner timeline to the first task start date for that resource.	functional requirement	1.5.2	PO-TP-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Team Planner shall synchronise its zoom level and day width with the Gantt Chart zoom.	functional requirement	1.5.3	PO-TP-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Right-clicking a task bar in the Team Planner shall display a context menu with actions: Split Task, Task Information, Add to Timeline, Remove from Timeline.	functional requirement	1.5.4	PO-TP-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.6 Secondary Calendar Support			1.6	1_6_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The Team Planner shall render secondary (regional holiday) calendar exceptions as semi-transparent yellow blocks within the resource swimlane, visually distinct from personal vacation blocks (orange).	functional requirement	1.6.1	PO-TP-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Hovering over a vacation or secondary calendar block in the Team Planner shall display a tooltip showing the exception name, date range (start – end), and – for secondary calendar blocks – the name of the source calendar (e.g. "Bayern").	functional requirement	1.6.2	PO-TP-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Drag-and-drop scheduling and task placement in the Team Planner shall treat secondary calendar exceptions as non-working days, preventing task drops on those days in the same way as personal vacation blocks.	functional requirement	1.6.3	PO-TP-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When collecting secondary calendar exceptions to render as yellow blocks in the Team Planner, the system shall exclude any exception whose date range is already present in the secondary calendar's parent calendar (the national/base holiday calendar); when the secondary calendar has no parent, the project default calendar shall be used as the reference. Only exceptions unique to the secondary calendar (not present in the parent or project default calendar) shall be rendered as yellow blocks, preventing double-rendering of national public holidays that are already shown via the primary resource calendar.	functional requirement	1.6.4	PO-TP-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When a secondary calendar exception has an empty or whitespace-only name, the Team Planner block label shall use the secondary calendar name alone (e.g. "Baden-Württemberg"); when the exception name is non-empty, the block label shall combine both in the format "<calendar_name>: <exception_name>" (e.g. "Baden-Württemberg: Heilige Drei Könige").	functional requirement	1.6.5	PO-TP-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When building the set of parent-calendar exception dates used to suppress duplicate rendering of secondary-calendar blocks in the Team Planner, the system shall include only exceptions whose name is non-empty and non-whitespace. Anonymous exceptions (getName() returns null, empty string, or whitespace only) shall be excluded from the suppression set. This ensures that secondary-calendar state holidays that share a start date with an unnamed school-holiday block ("Schulferien") in the parent calendar are not incorrectly hidden from the Team Planner view.	functional requirement	1.6.6	PO-TP-022.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
</OBJECTS>
